                <Activity ProgramAndActivitiesId="636" SortOrder="1">
                    <Heading/>
                    <Details>
                        <Detail SortOrder="1" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="993">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>https://www.ncpc.gov/ncpc/Main(T2)/About_Us(tr2)/About_Us(tr3)/History.html</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The National Capital Planning Commission was established as a
                                park planning agency by act of June 6, 1924, as amended (40 U.S.C.
                                8701 et seq.). Two years later, its role was expanded to include
                                comprehensive planning. In 1952, the National Capital Planning Act
                                designated the Commission as the central planning agency for the
                                Federal and District of Columbia governments.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                        <Detail SortOrder="2" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="994">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress/>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>In 1973, the National Capital Planning Act was amended by the
                                District of Columbia Home Rule Act, which made the mayor of the
                                District of Columbia the chief planner for the District and gave the
                                Commission specific authority for reviewing certain District
                                decisions. The Commission continues to serve, however, as the
                                central planning agency for the Federal Government in the National
                                Capital Region.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                        <Detail SortOrder="3" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="995">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>https://www.ncpc.gov/ncpc/Main(T2)/About_Us(tr2)/AboutUs.html</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Commission comprises five appointed and seven ex officio
                                members. Three citizen members, including the Chair, are appointed
                                by the President. The mayor of the District of Columbia appoints the
                                other two members. The Presidential appointees include one resident
                                from Maryland, one resident from Virginia, and one from anywhere
                                else in the United States. The two mayoral appointees must be
                                District of Columbia residents.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
            </ProgramAndActivity>
        </ProgramAndActivities>
